On 26 January, riots continued, with protesters numbering in their thousands, although no accurate estimate has yet been made. There was increased use of violence from both the protesters and the police, with one protester and one police official killed in Cairo.<ref name="np26jan"/> [[Suez]] experienced dramatic uprising, with many being fired upon by live ammunition, and both protesters and police being beaten.
